respond to actual cash outflows.","marks":[{"object":"mark","type":"italic","data":{}}]},{"object":"leaf","text":" This accounting and tax treatment of capital expenditures is one of the key reasons why earnings are not an accurate representation of cash flows. We will return to this issue in ","marks":[]}]},{"object":"inline","type":"reference-link","data":{"reference":"235fe190-44e1-11ed-8442-dbcbc27803ca"},"nodes":[{"object":"text","leaves":[{"object":"leaf","text":"Section 9.3","marks":[]}]}]},{"object":"text","leaves":[{"object":"leaf","text":".","marks":[]}]},{"object":"inline","type":"footnote","data":{"ref":"af193611-0a28-4141-8d9a-f93f96011a50","stage":{"ref":"0f93d373-d213-454f-b1e0-8c440ae0d889","sections":[{"ref":"8c9fcfd7-d840-4007-817e-753d56544161","rows":[{"ref":"6aeaa553-24f1-4a93-85ea-c05dffb54438","columns":[{"ref":"39d0e5a7-fb4c-4d15-8fdf-bddbaf7b655c","stageElements":[{"ref":"642c8ecf-5d3f-4807-9adc-713473f05473","type":"stage-element-text","value":{"object":"value","document":{"object":"document","data":{},"nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"button","ref":"a04fe946-b4b7-401c-9cff-d2a1048c65fa","nodes":[{"object":"block","type":"paragraph","ref":"b46338fa-4c5f-4f78-9f9c-6c91a76a9cf0","nodes":[{"object":"text","text":"Some students might note that for financial reporting, the asset should be depreciated to salvage value. For tax purposes, salvage value is always treated as zero, so this is the relevant method for capital budgeting.","marks":[]}],"data":{}}],"data":{}}]}}}]}]}]}]}},"nodes":[{"object":"text","leaves":[{"object":"leaf","text":"1","marks":[]}]}]},{"object":"text","leaves":[{"object":"leaf","text":"","marks":[]}]}]}]}},"config":{"cssClass":"","pluginConfigs":{}},"ref":"aa6151ed-3bcf-445e-aeb2-3f11e9a16a55"}],"ref":"fcfcb4c8-45cf-11ed-b667-a545ea5574ea"}],"ref":"fcfcb4c9-45cf-11ed-b667-a545ea5574ea"}],"rowsAreFullWidth":false,"backgroundImageUrl":"","cssClass":"","ref":"fcfcb4ca-45cf-11ed-b667-a545ea5574ea","backgroundImageAltText":""},